---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import QuickSummary from '../components/QuickSummary.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Getting Started" 
  description="First 30 days priorities and common mid-game mistakes for Last War: Survival. Clear, actionable advice for new players."
>
  <h1>Getting Started</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-[#8a96b0] max-w-3xl">Focus on the fundamentals. The first 30–60 days are about building momentum, not spreading yourself thin.</p>

  <QuickSummary>
    <p><strong>Rule #1:</strong> Pick one squad type (start with Tank for most players) and pour almost everything into it. Your HQ level and main squad strength unlock everything else.</p>
  </QuickSummary>

  <h2>First 30 Days Priorities</h2>
  
  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-base">Week 1–2</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-sm">
        <li>Rush your <strong>HQ</strong> as the primary power source</li>
        <li>Focus recruitment on early SSR heroes — SSR investment carries forward into UR promotion later, so it's not wasted</li>
        <li>Build your first mono-type squad (5 heroes of the same type)</li>
        <li>Complete all daily/weekly events for free resources</li>
        <li>Join an active alliance immediately</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-base">Week 3–4</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-sm">
        <li>Start pushing research that directly powers your main squad</li>
        <li>Unlock and upgrade your Troop Center for your chosen type</li>
        <li>Begin saving Legendary Recruitment Tickets (heroes) and Survivor Recruitment Tickets (survivors) for better pity timing</li>
        <li>Learn Doom Elite farming (bring Monica when you can)</li>
        <li>Stop upgrading every building evenly — be ruthless</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Common Mid-Game Mistakes</h2>
  <ul class="space-y-3">
    <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-[#f59e0b] font-bold mt-1">✕</span> <span><strong>Spreading resources too thin</strong> — Shards and gear across 8+ heroes. One strong squad beats three mediocre ones.</span></li>
    <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-[#f59e0b] font-bold mt-1">✕</span> <span><strong>Ignoring VS and Arms Race</strong> — These are the biggest consistent sources of progress for mid-game players.</span></li>
    <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-[#f59e0b] font-bold mt-1">✕</span> <span><strong>Upgrading every building evenly</strong> — Some buildings give almost nothing until much later. Be ruthless.</span></li>
    <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-[#f59e0b] font-bold mt-1">✕</span> <span><strong>Hoarding too much</strong> — Saving everything "for later" slows your actual power curve more than spending intelligently.</span></li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mt-8 p-4 bg-[#111a2e] border border-[#2a3854] rounded">
    <p class="text-sm"><strong>Next step:</strong> Go to <a href="/squad-building" class="text-[#f59e0b] hover:underline">Squad Building</a> and internalize the "Main Squad First" philosophy. Everything else becomes easier once you accept that your #1 squad carries most of your power for a long time.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Quick Resource Checklist (First 30 Days)</h2>
  <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
    <li>Complete all daily and weekly missions every day</li>
    <li>Participate in every VS and Arms Race event</li>
    <li>Join an active alliance as soon as possible</li>
    <li>Save Legendary Recruitment Tickets (heroes) and Survivor Recruitment Tickets for pity timing when possible</li>
    <li>Focus research and buildings on one squad type only</li>
  </ul>
</Layout>